---
import Layout from "@/layouts/main.astro"
import { buttonVariants } from "@/components/ui/button"
import { BASE } from "@/lib/url"
---

<Layout
  title="Where Builders Meet | Ruby — Discord Bot Commands"
  description="Ruby is the Where Builders Meet Discord bot. Discover all her commands: submit guild bases, find random builds, search catalog items, and more."
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl space-y-12">

    <!-- Hero -->
    <div class="space-y-3">
      <h1 class="font-heading text-2xl font-semibold flex items-center gap-2.5">
        <span class="text-2xl">🌸</span> Ruby
      </h1>
      <p class="text-muted-foreground text-sm leading-relaxed">
        Ruby is a small girl who lives inside the guild bases of Jiang Hu. She wanders between courtyards and rooftops, and she knows every build by heart.
        In the Discord server, she lives in <strong class="text-foreground">#ruby</strong> — ask her anything, or use one of her commands anywhere on the server.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Slash commands -->
    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-base font-medium">Slash commands</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
        Slash commands work anywhere on the server. Type <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 font-mono text-xs">/</code> in Discord to see them all with autocomplete.
      </p>

      <!-- Submissions -->
      <div class="space-y-2">
        <p class="text-xs font-medium text-muted-foreground uppercase tracking-wide">Submissions</p>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-border overflow-hidden divide-y divide-border">

          <div class="px-4 py-3 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-6 gap-y-1 items-start">
            <code class="font-mono text-sm text-foreground whitespace-nowrap">/submit-guild</code>
            <div class="space-y-1">
              <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Submit your own guild base to the showcase. A form opens where you fill in the name, builders, and Discord thread link.</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground/70 italic">Use this if you are the builder and want your base listed on the website.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="px-4 py-3 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-6 gap-y-1 items-start">
            <code class="font-mono text-sm text-foreground whitespace-nowrap">/submit-solo</code>
            <div class="space-y-1">
              <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Submit your solo construction to the showcase. Same form as guild, but for individual builds not tied to a guild.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="px-4 py-3 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-6 gap-y-1 items-start">
            <code class="font-mono text-sm text-foreground whitespace-nowrap">/scout-guild</code>
            <div class="space-y-1">
              <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Found a guild base you'd like to see on the website? Scout it here. A moderator will review and reference it for later.</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground/70 italic">You don't need to be the builder. Anyone can scout.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Personal -->
      <div class="space-y-2">
        <p class="text-xs font-medium text-muted-foreground uppercase tracking-wide">Personal</p>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-border overflow-hidden divide-y divide-border">

          <div class="px-4 py-3 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-6 gap-y-1 items-start">
            <code class="font-mono text-sm text-foreground whitespace-nowrap">/my-votes</code>
            <div class="space-y-1">
              <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Shows all the guild bases you have reacted to, grouped by reaction type and points. Only visible to you.</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground/70 italic">Also suggests guilds you haven't explored yet — great for broadening your voting spread.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="px-4 py-3 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-6 gap-y-1 items-start">
            <code class="font-mono text-sm text-foreground whitespace-nowrap">/builder &lt;member&gt;</code>
            <div class="space-y-1">
              <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Look up a server member's guild or solo base. Pick any member from the dropdown — only you see the result.</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground/70 italic">Example: <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 font-mono text-xs">/builder @Ahlyam</code></p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="px-4 py-3 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-6 gap-y-1 items-start">
            <code class="font-mono text-sm text-foreground whitespace-nowrap">/commands</code>
            <div class="space-y-1">
              <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Lists all of Ruby's commands with a short description. Only visible to you.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="px-4 py-3 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-6 gap-y-1 items-start">
            <code class="font-mono text-sm text-foreground whitespace-nowrap">/warning-list</code>
            <div class="space-y-1">
              <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Shows a guilds/leaders warning list for builders. Only visible to you.</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground/70 italic">See <a href={`${BASE}/how-it-works`} class="underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-foreground transition-colors">how it works</a> for context on why voting fairness matters.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Discovery -->
      <div class="space-y-2">
        <p class="text-xs font-medium text-muted-foreground uppercase tracking-wide">Discovery</p>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-border overflow-hidden divide-y divide-border">

          <div class="px-4 py-3 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-6 gap-y-1 items-start">
            <code class="font-mono text-sm text-foreground whitespace-nowrap">/random</code>
            <div class="space-y-1">
              <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Ruby picks a random guild base and posts its screenshot with a caption.</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground/70 italic">Great for discovering builds you've never seen before.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="px-4 py-3 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-6 gap-y-1 items-start">
            <code class="font-mono text-sm text-foreground whitespace-nowrap">/guild &lt;name&gt;</code>
            <div class="space-y-1">
              <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Share a guild base with its Discord thread link and website page. Starts typing to see autocomplete suggestions.</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground/70 italic">Example: <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 font-mono text-xs">/guild BlackFurry</code> — posts the card with links for that guild.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="px-4 py-3 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-6 gap-y-1 items-start">
            <code class="font-mono text-sm text-foreground whitespace-nowrap">/solo &lt;name&gt;</code>
            <div class="space-y-1">
              <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Same as <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 font-mono text-xs">/guild</code> but for solo constructions. Autocomplete included.</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground/70 italic">Example: <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 font-mono text-xs">/solo WINDXP Bridge</code></p>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>

    </section>

    <!-- Talking to Ruby -->
    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-base font-medium">Talking to Ruby</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
        Ruby reads every message in <strong class="text-foreground">#ruby</strong> that mentions her name or pings her. You don't need any special syntax — just talk to her naturally.
        She understands context, so you can ask follow-up questions.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-3">
        <p class="text-xs font-medium text-muted-foreground uppercase tracking-wide">Examples</p>

        <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-muted/30 divide-y divide-border overflow-hidden">
          <div class="px-4 py-3 space-y-1">
            <p class="text-sm font-mono text-foreground">ruby, show me a random guild</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">Ruby picks a surprise guild and posts its screenshot with a caption.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="px-4 py-3 space-y-1">
            <p class="text-sm font-mono text-foreground">@Ruby show me the BlackFurry</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">Ruby searches for a guild by name and posts a screenshot of it.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="px-4 py-3 space-y-1">
            <p class="text-sm font-mono text-foreground">ruby, are there any guilds with a Pikachu?</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">Ruby searches guild tags and lore for matches, then tells you what she finds.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="px-4 py-3 space-y-1">
            <p class="text-sm font-mono text-foreground">ruby, do you have any roof tiles in the catalog?</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">Ruby searches the catalog and posts matching item images.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="px-4 py-3 space-y-1">
            <p class="text-sm font-mono text-foreground">ruby, which guilds are tagged Nature?</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">Ruby lists all guilds that match that tag.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-xl border border-sky-200 dark:border-sky-800 bg-sky-50/60 dark:bg-sky-950/30 px-4 py-3 space-y-1">
        <p class="text-sm font-medium text-sky-700 dark:text-sky-300">Tip: say "random" for a quick shortcut</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Just typing <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 font-mono text-xs">ruby random</code> (or mentioning her and the word "random") skips the AI and instantly posts a surprise guild.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Finding guilds -->
    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-base font-medium">Finding guild bases in #ruby</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
        The #ruby channel is the best place to explore the showcase in conversation. Here are some ways people use it.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-3">

        <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-muted/20 px-4 py-4 space-y-3">
          <p class="text-sm font-medium">Browse by theme or tag</p>
          <div class="space-y-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
            <p class="font-mono text-foreground text-xs bg-muted rounded px-2 py-1.5">ruby, are there any guilds with mountains?</p>
            <p class="font-mono text-foreground text-xs bg-muted rounded px-2 py-1.5">ruby, which guilds are tagged Zen?</p>
            <p class="font-mono text-foreground text-xs bg-muted rounded px-2 py-1.5">ruby, show me guilds that feel like a hidden sect</p>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">Ruby searches guild names, tags, lore, and "what to visit" sections to find matches.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-muted/20 px-4 py-4 space-y-3">
          <p class="text-sm font-medium">Find a specific guild</p>
          <div class="space-y-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
            <p class="font-mono text-foreground text-xs bg-muted rounded px-2 py-1.5">ruby, show me the Iron Fist Valley</p>
            <p class="font-mono text-foreground text-xs bg-muted rounded px-2 py-1.5">@Ruby can you show me Eternal Snow Peak?</p>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">Ruby finds the guild by name and posts one of its screenshots directly into the channel.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-muted/20 px-4 py-4 space-y-3">
          <p class="text-sm font-medium">Explore the catalog</p>
          <div class="space-y-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
            <p class="font-mono text-foreground text-xs bg-muted rounded px-2 py-1.5">ruby, what lanterns do you have in the catalog?</p>
            <p class="font-mono text-foreground text-xs bg-muted rounded px-2 py-1.5">ruby, show me roof tiles</p>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">Ruby searches the building catalog and posts images of matching items, with a link to the full catalog page.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-muted/20 px-4 py-4 space-y-3">
          <p class="text-sm font-medium">Just be surprised</p>
          <div class="space-y-2">
            <p class="font-mono text-foreground text-xs bg-muted rounded px-2 py-1.5">ruby random</p>
            <p class="font-mono text-foreground text-xs bg-muted rounded px-2 py-1.5">/random</p>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">Ruby picks a random guild from the showcase and posts it with a caption she writes herself.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-muted/30 px-5 py-5 flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-start sm:items-center gap-4">
      <div class="flex-1">
        <p class="font-medium text-sm">Come say hi to Ruby</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground mt-0.5">She's waiting in #ruby on the community Discord.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-2 shrink-0">
        <a href="https://discord.gg/Qygt9u26Bn" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class={buttonVariants({ size: "lg" })} data-umami-event="discord_cta_click">Discord ↗</a>
        <a href={`${BASE}/contribute`} class={buttonVariants({ variant: "outline", size: "lg" })}>Contribute</a>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</Layout>
